Text.Value: Florrick chose shadow over light. Her betrayal burned deeper than the fires of Avernus.
Be in awe, Truest Soul. The new dawn will rise.
As I said. Baldur's Gate will ascend. Toril's first and only Grand City.

EditorData.NodeContext: recovers from faltering. (Toril = to-RIL)

Text.Value: Punished? Meaning what, exactly?

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken as an aside to player - soft but sharp, suddenly tense. You want to know what became of an ally.

Text.Value: How do Baldurans punish traitors? Hanging? Dismemberment? I hope we get to see.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: My dearest boy. The Hells have touched you. But you've come to me - just as Gortash said you would. A True Soul no less.
*For a brief moment, uncertainty clouds his mind, then dissipates. The Astral Prism vibrates in concord.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ravengard touches his head for a brief moment. He is taken aback for a moment.

Text.Value: I've stilled her tongue. That's the end of the matter.
Have you come to behold the new dawn?
The illithids have not erased him entire. Perhaps there is hope yet.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Connect with Ravengard's parasite to seek information about Florrick.

EditorData.logicalname: Tadpoled player only - Asked about Florrick, hasn't found her in prison

Text.Value: *You are unable to penetrate Ravengard's mind.*
*Your tadpole seizes, the Prism stills. Ravengard's empty eyes meet yours.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ravengard shakes his head, regaining control.

Text.Value: *The Duke wants to keep Florrick's location a secret. Little does he know that you've already found and freed her.*
Go. Be Her justice.
The sun rises, my boy, my True Soul. Are you ready?
The sun rises, True Soul. Are you ready?
Ravengard is still alive, trapped in his own mind. Just as I was.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player., with sympathy for Ravengard. She wouldn't wish this on her worst enemy

Text.Value: Leave.
Indeed. The Absolute will bring glory upon this fair city.
Don't you understand? You are infected with an illithid parasite.
Father and son, unstoppable generals. Together, we will usher in a new dawn.
Father and son, unstoppable generals. You and your allies will usher in a new dawn.
Punished?! Gods. Don't want to imagine what that entails. Maybe there's still time to find her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Not just glory. Paradise.
So much to teach, and so much to learn.
'New dawn'? Is that what you call the tyranny the Absolute brings to Baldur's Gate?
*First comes a vision of terror. The city of Baldur's Gate taken by illithids.*
Help me? Ah - the black widow caught you in her web.
Have we finished, then?
Leave.
*Your father, once the Grand Duke, now a pawn in the Absolute's game. Your infected minds smoulder in each others' presence.*
The Absolute's time has come. She will bring glory to the city.
My dearest boy. The Hells have touched you. But you've come to me - just as Gortash said you would.
Punished? Then Florrick's been captured. Or worse.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: I'm here to help you. Florrick sent me.
My dearest boy, my blood and my pride. You've come to me - just as Gortash said you would. A True Soul no less.
What nonsense is this. I...
And you, Gortash and I will ignite the final spark, my son.
And it will be Gortash who ignites the final spark.
*Behind Ravengard's eyes, something stirs. A spark of life, of self.*
Ravengard - the real Ravengard - is in there somewhere. We can't give up on him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: But Baldur's Gate will soon burn bright. A beacon to light the heavens.
*Ravengard thrusts you from his mind.*
A fresh mind, still untouched. You have not yet heard the Absolute's voice.
My dearest boy, my blood and my pride. You've come to me - just as Gortash said you would.
*Your heart stirs. Despite Ravengard's words, Helm's watchful gaze remains upon you.*
*Tyr's fury glows within you. Despite Ravengard's words, the Lord of Justice has remained loyal to you, as you have to him.*
*Within Ravengard's memories, you find Counsellor Florrick. She is confined in a cell, right here in Wyrm's Rock.*
Gortash is a tyrant. This 'new dawn' is a lie.
Faerûn suffers in darkness. Tyr has abandoned us; Helm's eye has strayed.
She's been punished for her lies. Don't let her get to you.
You, Gortash and I will ignite the final spark, my son. And that is the greatest of goods.
Gortash and I will ignite the final spark. And that, True Soul, is the greatest of goods.
Let Her light shine.
My own son, touched by the Hells - yet as true a soul as there ever was.
My own son, as true a soul as ever there was.
Truest of Souls. Bathed in Her light.

EditorData.NodeContext: Creeply magnanimous greeting

Text.Value: The real Ravengard's still in there - and he wants out.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: *The Prism quivers once more. Ravengard falters.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Ravengard shakes his head, trying to rid it of his inner turmoil.

Text.Value: Punished? Gods - what has he done?

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: No - this isn't him. This is the tadpole talking.

EditorData.NodeContext: Upset at seeing his father being controlled by the Absolute

Text.Value: What is a hero, my son, if not an actor for the greater good?
What is a hero, if not an actor for the greater good?
Ignore Ravengard's hesitation.
*The Duke wants to keep Florrick's location a secret. Little does he know that you've already found her.*
My father, my hero. I'll save you from the Absolute's thrall.
Leave.
What have you done to Florrick?
Punished? Florrick must be locked up somewhere - assuming she's still alive.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Why do you say this? Only the shadows would name the sun a tyrant.
*Ravengard's eyes grow empty again. Once again, he speaks coolly and calmly.*
Her sun will rise. Our future is decided.
By the gods, what have they made of the city's great hero?
Leave the duke's mind unexplored.
Why do I get the feeling the punishment will be far, far worse than the crime?

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Be in awe, Truest Soul. The new dawn will rise.
The true Ravengard is still clinging on, somewhere in that mind. It might not be too late for him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Ravengard hasn't given up yet. His true self is still in there, and could yet be saved.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: So, the real man is still in there somewhere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: *There is a fleeting connection. Your parasite communes with his, then falls quiet.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Slight mind meld just through the course of the node.

Text.Value: Father, please. Come back to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not too pleading.

Text.Value: Don't speak such nonsense.
*The true Ravengard lurks somewhere in this infected mind, seeking freedom - seeking victory.*

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: When he says 'punished' do you think he means 'locked up' or 'brutally murdered'?

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: The true Ravengard still lives within. If Minsc could be freed from his fleshy prison, then so can the Duke!

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: 'Punished'...? That is meaning more than a spanking, in a place such as this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Punished? Then Florrick has been captured... or perhaps is no more.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Our time has come, son. Together, we will usher in a new dawn.
The true Ravengard remains in there somewhere. Perhaps he can yet be restored.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken softly as an aside to player.

Text.Value: Lord Gortash expects you.
Father...
...help me...

EditorData.NodeContext: The real Ravengard breaks through his brainwashing, just for a moment.

Text.Value: It's not a good time.
Call on your tadpole. Explore Ravengard's uncertainty.
